<p>Using genome-wide CRISPR-Cas9 screens and an in vivo system modeling of antigen-experienced CD4+ T cell recruitment and proliferation during a localized immune response, we identified suppressor of cytokine signaling 1 (SOCS1) as a major nonredundant checkpoint imposing a brake on CD4+ T cell proliferation.
<br /></p>


